of the modern Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 568, \"end\": 573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999991508142525, \"rank\": 8.491865439193464e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Coubertin first conceived the revival of this ancient Greek tradition in the late 19th century, he imagined a scene where nations celebrated friendly internationalism by playing sports together.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 706, \"end\": 719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9950872003007721, \"rank\": 0.00493281405282516, \"text\": \"ancient Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His Olympic idealism provides the foundation for theOlympic charter, a set of rules and guidelines for the organisation of the Olympic Games that emphasise international fraternity and solidarity.\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 1051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1992, the International Olympic Committee (IOC) moved to uphold Coubertin's legacy by renewing the tradition of thesacred truceassociated with the ancient Olympics.\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1066, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1066, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic truce calls for the cessation of hostilities between warring nations during the Olympic Games and beyond.\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic truce has contributed to peace before - albeit only fleetingly.\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During the opening ceremony of the 2018 Winter Olympic Games in Pyeongchang, South Korea, the South and North Korean delegations marched into the stadiumtogetherunder the single flag of the Korean peninsula.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1480, \"end\": 1491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.89271769741042, \"rank\": 0.1201749476913067, \"text\": \"Pyeongchang\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_Winter_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.342684804277225e-13, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.7722297845824416, \"rank\": 0.25495662724079204, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1606, \"end\": 1622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Korean peninsula\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They also fielded a unified Korean ice hockey team for this competition.\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.7722297845824416, \"rank\": 0.25495662724079204, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:The Winter Olympics and the two Koreas: how sport diplomacy could save the world  The IOChopesthat the forthcoming Olympics will be a moment for world peace.\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But with the Paris Olympic torch relay starting next month, the world is plagued with conflict and animosity.\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1975, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1879, \"end\": 1884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999991508142525, \"rank\": 8.491865439193464e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1885, \"end\": 1898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.305607038552319e-23, \"text\": \"Olympic torch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And tensions in eastern Europe and the Middle East show no sign of easing.\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Olympics will take place amid geopolitical turmoil.\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These conflicts will affect the Olympic Games and throw into question the capacity of sport to reduce tension between nations.\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moscow ordered its army to invade Ukraine four days after the end of the 2022 Winter Olympics in Beijing.\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2241, \"end\": 2247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999999944757292, \"rank\": 5.524488160171779e-09, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}, {\"begin\": 2275, \"end\": 2282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999975602675225, \"rank\": 2.3911290208733576e-06, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2338, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"score\": 0.9625207832373357, \"rank\": 0.038354387573588285, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC considered this aggression a violation of the Olympic truce and subsequentlybannedRussian athletes from participating in the Paris Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2351, \"end\": 2354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.473291529453738e-43, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Russia was unhappy with this decision.\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2502, \"end\": 2508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999580710978223, \"rank\": 2.816357181117914e-05, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Itcondemnedthe IOC as being biased towards the west and even appealed to the Court of Arbitration for Sport against the suspension.\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 2672, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But in February 2024, the court eventuallyupheldthe IOC's position.\", \"from\": 2673, \"to\": 2740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.473291529453738e-43, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Russian athletes will not be absent from the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2742, \"end\": 2749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.6224771431241063, \"rank\": 0.6036276382756228, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC allows them to take part in the competition not as a state delegation but as neutral individuals.\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2902, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2801, \"end\": 2804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.473291529453738e-43, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ukraine finds this situation unacceptable,arguingthat neutrality cannot remove Russian identity from the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 3017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2903, \"end\": 2910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999975602675225, \"rank\": 2.3911290208733576e-06, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2982, \"end\": 2989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.6224771431241063, \"rank\": 0.6036276382756228, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC has denounced the Russian occupation of Ukrainian territories.\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3023, \"end\": 3026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.473291529453738e-43, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3045, \"end\": 3052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.6224771431241063, \"rank\": 0.6036276382756228, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3067, \"end\": 3076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9087141190808165, \"rank\": 0.1003776413791855, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it also admits the complexity of this geopolitical conflict, and acknowledges that its best approach would be to keep impartiality on this matter.\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ukraine responded by implementing apolicyfor its athletes to boycott any contests involving Russians at Paris 2024, although it later lifted this rule.\", \"from\": 3241, \"to\": 3392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3241, \"end\": 3248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999975602675225, \"rank\": 2.3911290208733576e-06, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 3333, \"end\": 3341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999840269267821, \"rank\": 9.400213860648725e-06, \"text\": \"Russians\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The war between Israel and Hamas will further complicate the 2024 Olympics, with Olympic officials poised to face allegations of inconsistency concerning Israeli athletes.\", \"from\": 3394, \"to\": 3565, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3410, \"end\": 3416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1238804879212143e-22, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 3421, \"end\": 3426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4359592544722756e-14, \"text\": \"Hamas\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\"}, {\"begin\": 3548, \"end\": 3555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999995487001906, \"rank\": 3.6248611549797226e-07, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This conflict is no less brutal than the war between Ukraine and Russia.\", \"from\": 3567, \"to\": 3639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3620, \"end\": 3627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999975602675225, \"rank\": 2.3911290208733576e-06, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 3632, \"end\": 3638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999580710978223, \"rank\": 2.816357181117914e-05, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the Hamas-run health ministry, more than 30,000 people have beenkilledin Gaza since the start of the war.\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3726, \"end\": 3730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9998231492379963, \"rank\": 0.00017688204372039298, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And there is alsoevidencethat Israeli forces have committed war crimes in the Gaza Strip.\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3789, \"end\": 3796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999995487001906, \"rank\": 3.6248611549797226e-07, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 3837, \"end\": 3847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.074141293372114e-12, \"text\": \"Gaza Strip\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the resolution for the Olympic truce of Paris 2024 singles out the suspension of Russia and does not contain a single word on the violence in Israel and Palestine.\", \"from\": 3850, \"to\": 4022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3899, \"end\": 3909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.614556781036149e-24, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3940, \"end\": 3946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999580710978223, \"rank\": 2.816357181117914e-05, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4001, \"end\": 4007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1238804879212143e-22, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 4012, \"end\": 4021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.9442164414979197, \"rank\": 0.05907920689568382, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These two warring parties can participate in the Olympics - though the strictblockadeof the Gaza Strip will make it hard for Palestinians to take part in the games.\", \"from\": 4024, \"to\": 4188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4116, \"end\": 4126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.074141293372114e-12, \"text\": \"Gaza Strip\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 4149, \"end\": 4161, \"title\"